<html metal:use-macro="context/@@marketing_about_template/master">
<body>
  <h2 metal:fill-slot="application">Translations</h2>

  <metal:contents fill-slot="contents">
    <h2 class="headline">Cut the time it takes to translate your software</h2>

    <table id="features">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <th>Anyone can translate</th>
          <th>Intelligent suggestions</th>
          <th>Supports GetText</th>
          <th>Translation collaboration</th>
        </tr>
        <tr class="screenshots">
          <td><img src="/+icing/translations-feature1.png"
                   alt="Feature 1 Screenshot" /></td>
          <td><img src="/+icing/translations-feature2.png"
                   alt="Feature 2 Screenshot" /></td>
          <td><img src="/+icing/translations-feature3.png"
                   alt="Feature 3 Screenshot" /></td>
          <td><img src="/+icing/translations-feature4.png"
                   alt="Feature 4 Screenshot" /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Simple web interface that's ideal for non-developers.</td>
          <td>Automatic suggestions from 750,000 translated strings.</td>
          <td>Works with standard .pot, .po and .mo files.</td>
          <td>Collaborate with 19,000 translators in 235 languages.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div id="content">
      <div class="intro">
        <h3>About Launchpad Translations</h3>

        <p>Translators shouldn't have to be coders. Launchpad shields
           translators from low-level complexities, whilst working with
           standard .pot, .po and .mo files.
        </p>

        <p>Automatic suggestions, from a library of 750,000 translated
           strings, and a community of 19,000 registered translators can
           radically cut the time required to localise your project into many
           languages.
        </p>

        <p>Launchpad keeps track of the translations for each major version of
           a project separately, allowing translators to continue to improve
           the translations of your stable releases while others start work on
           newer versions that are still in development.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div> <!-- content -->
  </metal:contents>
</body>
</html>
